=\"ltr\" id=\"mchl732d3c0a\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic dark-mode-enabled\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mchl732d3c0a\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Finder.png\"></figure><h1>Pick up where you left off with Handoff on Mac</h1><p>With Handoff, you can start something on one Apple device (Mac, iPhone, iPad, or Apple Watch) and then seamlessly pick it up on another device. For example, start answering an email on your iPhone, then finish it in Mail on your Mac. You can use Handoff with many Apple apps—for example, Calendar, Contacts, Pages, and Safari. Some third-party apps may also work with Handoff.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2b5216c94da378c9f25823900a8bb1ee.png\" alt=\"An app’s Handoff icon from iPhone in the Dock.\" height=\"117\" width=\"270\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0014_Handoff.png\"></figure><p>To use Handoff, your Apple devices must meet <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=continuity&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOSE229DF1E&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Continuity</a> system requirements. They must also have Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and Handoff turned on in System Settings (on your Mac) and in Settings (on your iOS and iPadOS devices). You must be <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=sign-in-with-your-apple-id&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOS0159E54B&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">signed in with the same Apple ID</a> on all your devices. </p><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Tip\"><strong class=\"tip\">Tip: </strong>When Handoff is on, you can <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=copy-and-paste-between-devices&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL70368996&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">use Universal Clipboard</a> to copy and paste text, images, photos, and videos across devices. You can also copy files between Mac computers.</p></div><div id=\"apd98397effbea64\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-apd98397effbea64\" class=\"Name\">Turn Handoff on or off</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-apd98397effbea64\"><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Note\"><em>Note: </em>If a Handoff option isn’t available on your device, it doesn’t work with Handoff.</p></div><ul><li><p><em>On your Mac: </em>Choose Apple menu <picture><source media=\"(not all)\" srcset=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/0e2c53fa5a413cc7ff5099226fb50188.png\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11~dark.png\"></source><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2f77cc85238452e25cb517130188bf99.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"24\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11.png\"></picture> &gt; System Settings, click General <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/7c4faef8373d3d73052729c76d485046.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_General.png\"> in the sidebar, click AirDrop &amp; Handoff on the right, then turn “Allow Handoff between this Mac and your iCloud devices” on or off. (You may need to scroll down.)</p><p><a href=\"x-apple.systempreferences:com.apple.AirDrop-Handoff-Settings.extension\" class=\"URL\">Open AirDrop &amp; Handoff settings for me</a></p></li><li><p><em>On iPad, iPhone, or iPod touch: </em>Go to Settings &gt; General &gt; AirPlay &amp; Handoff, then turn Handoff on or off.</p></li><li><p><em>On Apple Watch: </em>Open the Apple Watch app on iPhone, go to My Watch &gt; General, then turn Enable Handoff on or off.</p></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"apd453437190cfe4\" class=\"Task\"><h2 aria-controls=\"aria-apd453437190cfe4\" class=\"Name\">Hand off between devices</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-apd453437190cfe4\"><ul><li><p><em>From your Mac to an iOS or iPadOS device: </em>The Handoff icon of the app you’re using on your Mac appears on your iPhone (at the bottom of the app switcher) or your iPad or iPod touch (at the end of the Dock). Tap to continue working in the app.</p></li><li><p><em>From an iOS or iPadOS device or Apple Watch to your Mac: </em>The Handoff icon of the app you’re using on your iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, or Apple Watch appears on your Mac near the right end of the Dock (or the bottom, depending on the Dock position). Click the icon to continue working in the app.</p><p>You can also press Command-Tab to <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=work-with-app-windows&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2469&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">quickly switch to the app</a> that has the Handoff icon.</p></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=work-across-devices-using-continuity&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL1D734309&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use Continuity to work across Apple devices</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=turn-bluetooth-on-or-off&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=BLTH1008&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Turn Bluetooth on or off on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=sign-in-or-out-of-your-apple-id-on-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLA99DC8DA&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Sign in or out of your Apple ID on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/HT204681\" class=\"URL\">Apple Support article: Use Continuity to connect your Mac, iPhone, iPad, iPod touch, and Apple Watch</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","DisplayVersion/macOS Ventura 13","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ContentMode/liveContent","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON","ArchivalStatus/Archived","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"120736"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"135880"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"135315"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName":"plat